### What happened?

I need to read multiple tags from ControlLogix 1756-L71, for example 1000 tags,  and I found it quite slow, so i debug into the driver source code,  and it appears that the 247th line in `EipProtocolLogic.java` always trigged.
```java
if ((long) response.getStatus() == CIPStatus.ServiceNotSupported.getValue()) {
                    context.fireConnected();   // 247th line
                    return;
                } else if ((long) response.getStatus() != CIPStatus.Success.getValue()) {
                    throw new PlcRuntimeException("Got status code while polling for supported CIP attributes [" + response.getStatus() + "]");
                }
                if (response.getAttributes() != null) {
                    for (Integer classId : response.getAttributes().getClassId()) {
                        if (CIPClassID.enumForValue(classId) == CIPClassID.MessageRouter) {
                            this.useMessageRouter = true;     // never run
                        }
                        if (CIPClassID.enumForValue(classId) == CIPClassID.ConnectionManager) {
                            this.useConnectionManager = true;   // nerver run
                        }
                    }
                }
```
which means the CIP service is not supported,  and the 665th line in the same file will always be trigged,
```java
    public CompletableFuture<PlcReadResponse> read(PlcReadRequest readRequest) {
        CompletableFuture<PlcReadResponse> future;
        if (!this.useMessageRouter && !this.useConnectionManager) {
            future = readWithoutMessageRouter(readRequest);       # 665th line,  read tag one by one 
        } else if (this.useMessageRouter && !this.useConnectionManager) {
            future = readWithoutConnectionManager(readRequest);  # never run, read tags at one request, high efficient
        } else {
            future = readWithConnectionManager(readRequest);     # never run,  read tags at one request, high efficient
        }
        return future;
    }
```
the method `readWithoutMessageRouter` reads tags one by one, which cause significant decrease in efficiency. the method `readWithoutConnectionManager` and `readWithConnectionManager` are reading tags at one request, but they will never be triggered.

there is a similar bug reported and the author gives a solution. [Unable to Read from Allen-Bradley 1756-L73 A ControlLogix PLC](https://github.com/libplctag/libplctag/issues/437#issue-1904212613)  

